            "description": "For every boxershort an every 700 liters of water is used in the cotton production. This ridiculously high amount of water is for 42 percent irrigated from local rivers and lakes. This has an enormous impact on nature, the environment and locals who are dependent on these water sources. To promote 'rainfed' organic cotton with a GOTS certification, we organised an underwear right through the city centre of Amsterdam. All runners were sponsered with sustainable underwear. About 70 youth participated in the run and the event got international media attention.",
